messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /api/products/{id}/reviews

- allMethods: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- server.js mounts the product routes at the prefix /api/products (app.use('/api/products', productRoutes)).
- routes/productRoutes.js registers the route router.route('/:id/reviews').post(protect, checkObjectId, createProductReview); so the only HTTP method explicitly defined for that path is POST (with protect and checkObjectId middleware).
- controllers/productController.js implements createProductReview and documents it as handling POST /api/products/:id/reviews.
- No handlers for GET, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, OPTIONS, TRACE, or HEAD are defined for this exact path. Express does not implicitly expose those methods for a POST-only route (HEAD is only automatically handled when a GET route exists), so they are marked false.
- allMethods is false because there is no code allowing all methods.
